{
  "description": "Composite Layer 4 (false-positive mitigation): a fully aligned, trusted message. From, Message-ID, Reply-To, Return-Path, smtp.mailfrom, DKIM header.d, and DMARC header.from all resolve to example.com and every method passes, so the base layer is silent. The composite layer adds one info-severity composite.alignedAuthenticationConfirmed — the single positive marker a caller needs to confidently lower a score. It gates on real aligned trusted authentication for the visible From, which a spoofer of another domain cannot produce, so it cannot be used to launder a forgery.",
  "input": {
    "headers": {
      "from": "Example Sender <notice@example.com>",
      "message-id": "<id@example.com>",
      "reply-to": "<notice@example.com>",
      "return-path": "<notice@example.com>",
      "authentication-results": [
        "mx.example.net; dmarc=pass header.from=example.com; spf=pass smtp.mailfrom=example.com; dkim=pass header.d=example.com"
      ]
    },
    "options": {
      "trustedAuthservIds": ["mx.example.net"]
    }
  },
  "expected": {
